Some things to be aware of:
* This way of intercommunication is deprecated as of API 30.
* Sotrage access infrastructure has changes and specific steps have to be take to gain regular internal storage access privileges. Hence, Unless we use MediaStore, ROOM, or SAF, we&#39;ll get ```NullPointerException``` in most cases; or requested sotrage locations will just create a directory of that name in our com.appd.app&#39;s files directory and all interaction will be done from that source.


Anyway, the current method of getting input from called Activity:

###### Imports
```
import androidx.activity.result.ActivityResult;
import androidx.activity.result.ActivityResultCallback;
import androidx.activity.result.ActivityResultLauncher;
import androidx.activity.result.contract.ActivityResultContracts;
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;
import android.content.Intent;
```

###### Liaison object
```
ActivityResultLauncher&lt;Intent&gt; activityForResultLauncher;
activityForResultLauncher = registerForActivityResult(new ActivityResultContracts.StartActivityForResult(), new ActivityResultCallback&lt;ActivityResult&gt;()
{
	@Override
	public void onActivityResult(ActivityResult result)
	{
		if(result.getResultCode() == RESULT_OK)
		{
			Intent data = result.getData();

			// handle business...
		}
	}
});
```

* The LAMBDA variation of the above code
	```
	ActivityResultLauncher&lt;Intent&gt; activityForResultLauncher;
	activityForResultLauncher = registerForActivityResult(new ActivityResultContracts.StartActivityForResult(), result-&gt;
	{
	if(result.getResultCode() == RESULT_OK)
	{
	intentData = result.getData();

	// handle business...
	}
	});
	```
###### Launch phase
* Then it is only a matter of using that object for handling comms
  ```
  activityForResultLauncher.launch(someIntent);
  ```
* Usually I&#39;d return ```RESULT_OK``` from _called_ Activity when I am done with my work there and invoke ```finish()``` on it. Then I&#39;m back to the _caller_ Activity and we&#39;re able to proceed resuming at our overriden ```onActivityResult``` method section.
* The older methods aren&#39;t necessary anymore.

